<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-3632] ConsumerLag metrics persist after partition migration</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-3632</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When a partition is migrated away from a broker, the ConsumerLag metric for the topic/partition gets &apos;stuck&apos; at the current value. The only way to remove the metric is to restart the broker.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This appears to be because in AbstractFetcherThread.scala there is no way of removing a metric. See...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;FetcherLagStats(metricId: ClientIdAndBroker) { 
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;private&lt;/span&gt; val valueFactory = (k: ClientIdTopicPartition) =&amp;gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; FetcherLagMetrics(k) 
val stats = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Pool[ClientIdTopicPartition, FetcherLagMetrics](Some(valueFactory))

def getFetcherLagStats(topic: &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;, partitionId: Int): FetcherLagMetrics = { 
stats.getAndMaybePut(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; ClientIdTopicPartition(metricId.clientId, topic, partitionId)) 
} 
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
